summary: An email from an FBI supervisory special agent requesting assistance to execute a search warrant at Jeffrey Epstein's residence for digital media and computer equipment, noting that most of the agent's squad is in Florida interviewing victims.

keyFacts: The FBI planned to execute a search warrant at Jeffrey Epstein's residence on or around July 11, 2019, targeting digital media and computer equipment.
Most of the FBI squad (C-20 Crimes Against Children/Human Trafficking) was in Florida interviewing victims at the time, creating a need for additional personnel.
The email demonstrates active FBI investigation into Epstein in July 2019, focusing on digital evidence and victim interviews.
